# Steps to reproduce

```powershell
Add-Type -Type @' 

    public interface IMyClass 
    {
        void MyMethod();
    }

    public class MyClass : IMyClass
    { 
        public MyClass()
        {
        
        }
        
        public void MyMethod() 
        { 
            System.Console.WriteLine("MyMethod");
        } 
    } 

    public static class AStaticClass
    { 
        public static void StaticMethod(IMyClass myclass) 
        { 
            myclass.MyMethod();
        } 
    } 
'@

class MyInheritedClass : MyClass {
    MyMethod() {
        Write-Host "PowerShell won!"
    }
}

[AStaticClass]::StaticMethod([MyInheritedClass]::new())

```

# Expected behavior

```none
'MyInheritedClass .MyMethod()': cannot override inherited member 'MyClass.MyMethod()' because it is not marked virtual, abstract, or override
```

# Actual behavior

```none
MyMethod
```

